review.description:
if you like Patsy's you'll like it here. the wait was pretty long..almost felt like a bathroom line. still, i walked out with my belly full of pepperoni pizza made from fresh ingredients, and the biggest grin on my face you'd think i just crapped money. (sorry, i dont know how else to describe it)

i wouldn't say large groups a good idea, groups of 2's and 3's get in a lot faster than say...seven..if you don't have the patience to enjoy this historic pizzeria, then scat and give those who do more room to eat! 

great service, great food, great fun.
